    thinking: "**Designing the Application**\n\nOkay, I\'ve absorbed the Gemini API knowledge! Now, the real challenge begins: designing a killer full-stack application. The core user need is clear: they encountered an unexpected error and want to resume the task that they were doing. I am working on the requirements.\n\n\n**Defining the Core Application**\n\nI\'ve decided to build a complete React, Express, and Tailwind CSS workspace, leveraging Gemini\'s capabilities. I believe a high-quality, full-stack app like this will be incredibly valuable to users, especially after encountering an error. Considering the potential, I\'m leaning toward an application name: \"OmniMind Studio\" or \"AI Creative Suite.\" I\'m also planning the modules.\n\n\n**Refining The Components**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the components for the \"ZenSpace\" application. Specifically, I\'m fleshing out the left sidebar. It will have a collapsible drawer that contains tabs for different workspace functions. The tabs I\'m considering are a \"Zen Editor\" for notes with an AI co-author, and an \"Aether Grounding\" tool for smart search. The user experience and visual design are primary considerations.\n\n\n**Visualizing Application Features**\n\nI\'m now adding features to the application. I have decided to include an image canvas to generate illustrations with `gemini-2.5-flash-image`. The grounding citations will be presented as cards, and a productivity dashboard will show task stats and focus timers. Since we\'re using the Gemini API, I\'m ensuring it\'s a full-stack application for security.\n\n\n**Defining the Tech Stack**\n\nI am now focusing on setting up the full-stack architecture. I\'ve outlined the critical requirements, including updating the `package.json` scripts for development, building, and starting the application, configuring the server with Vite middleware, and implementing API endpoints for Gemini integration. I am also planning the configuration of the `.env.example` file.