  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing Server Backend**\n\nOkay, I\'m now crafting the `server.ts` backend. My focus is handling Gemini API calls securely with `@google/genai`, mirroring the `gemini_api` skill\'s structure. I\'m currently reviewing the necessary backend endpoints: `/api/notes/coauthor`.\n\n\n**Defining API Endpoints**\n\nI\'m now solidifying the `/api/research` endpoint. It leverages Google Search grounding with `gemini-3.5-flash`, mirroring the `gemini_api` skill. I\'m extracting grounding metadata, including web search queries and chunks (URIs and titles). The backend will return `{ text, chunks, searchQueries }` for client-side display. This is a robust approach, I\'m very happy with how this is turning out!\n\n\n**Implementing Image Generation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the `/api/visualize` endpoint, using `gemini-2.5-flash-image` for image generation. I\'m extracting the image generation logic from the `gemini_api` skill, particularly how to set the aspect ratio via `imageConfig`, defaulting to \"1:1\" if not specified. I also need to figure out how to extract the base64 image data from the response; there\'s a loop that accesses `inlineData.data`, which I will need to use.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the full-stack server file `/server.ts` using Express. This server will handle our lazy-loaded Gemini API requests for research grounding, note co-authoring, and image generation, and it will mount the Vite development middleware when in development."
